#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.22:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Kosala "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 22. Ayyikāsutta → ayyakāsuttaṃ (bj, pts2) | ayyakā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Ayyikāsutta "
msgstr "22. Grandmother "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.97, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.22:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.22:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala sat to one side, and the Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "sn3.22:1.3"
msgid "“handa kuto nu tvaṃ, mahārāja, āgacchasi divādivassā”ti? "
msgstr "“So, great king, where are you coming from in the middle of the day?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.217, sc2
msgctxt "sn3.22:2.1"
msgid "“Ayyikā me, bhante, kālaṅkatā jiṇṇā vuḍḍhā mahallikā addhagatā vayoanuppattā vīsavassasatikā jātiyā. "
msgstr "“Sir, my grandmother has passed away. She was old, elderly and senior. She was advanced in years and had reached the final stage of life; she was a hundred and twenty years old. "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.2"
msgid "Ayyikā kho pana me, bhante, piyā hoti manāpā. "
msgstr "But I loved my grandmother; she was dear to me. "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.3"
msgid "Hatthiratanena cepāhaṃ, bhante, labheyyaṃ ‘mā me ayyikā kālamakāsī’ti, hatthiratanampāhaṃ dadeyyaṃ: "
msgstr "If by giving away the elephant treasure I could get my grandmother back, I’d do it. "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.4"
msgid "‘mā me ayyikā kālamakāsī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.5"
msgid "Assaratanena cepāhaṃ, bhante, labheyyaṃ ‘mā me ayyikā kālamakāsī’ti, assaratanampāhaṃ dadeyyaṃ: "
msgstr "If by giving away the horse treasure I could get my grandmother back, I’d do it. "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.6"
msgid "‘mā me ayyikā kālamakāsī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.7"
msgid "Gāmavarena cepāhaṃ, bhante, labheyyaṃ ‘mā me ayyikā kālamakāsī’ti, gāmavarampāhaṃ dadeyyaṃ: "
msgstr "If by giving away a prize village I could get my grandmother back, I’d do it. "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.8"
msgid "‘mā me ayyikā kālamakāsī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: Janapadapadesena → janapadena (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.22:2.9"
msgid "Janapadapadesena cepāhaṃ, bhante, labheyyaṃ ‘mā me ayyikā kālamakāsī’ti, janapadapadesampāhaṃ dadeyyaṃ: "
msgstr "If by giving away the whole country I could get my grandmother back, I’d do it.” "

# NOTE: MS should close the king’s speech here.
msgctxt "sn3.22:2.10"
msgid "‘mā me ayyikā kālamakāsī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.22:2.11"
msgid "‘Sabbe sattā, mahārāja, maraṇadhammā maraṇapariyosānā maraṇaṃ anatītā’ti. "
msgstr "“Great king, all sentient beings are liable to die. Death is their end; they’re not exempt from death.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.22:2.12"
msgid "‘Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing, "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.13"
msgid "Yāvasubhāsitamidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā—"
msgstr "how well said this was by the Buddha: "

msgctxt "sn3.22:2.14"
msgid "sabbe sattā maraṇadhammā maraṇapariyosānā maraṇaṃ anatītā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘All sentient beings are liable to die. Death is their end; they’re not exempt from death.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.218, sc3
msgctxt "sn3.22:3.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, mahārāja, evametaṃ, mahārāja. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, great king! That’s so true! "

msgctxt "sn3.22:3.2"
msgid "Sabbe sattā maraṇadhammā maraṇapariyosānā maraṇaṃ anatītā. "
msgstr "All sentient beings are liable to die. Death is their end; they’re not exempt from death. "

msgctxt "sn3.22:3.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, mahārāja, yāni kānici kumbhakārabhājanāni āmakāni ceva pakkāni ca sabbāni tāni bhedanadhammāni bhedanapariyosānāni bhedanaṃ anatītāni; "
msgstr "It’s like the vessels made by potters. Whatever kind they are, whether baked or unbaked, all of them are liable to break apart. Breaking is their end; they’re not exempt from breakage. "

msgctxt "sn3.22:3.4"
msgid "evameva kho, mahārāja, sabbe sattā maraṇadhammā maraṇapariyosānā maraṇaṃ anatītā”ti. "
msgstr "In the same way, all sentient beings are liable to die. Death is their end; they’re not exempt from death.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.22:3.5"
msgid "Idamavoca … pe … "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. … "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn3.22:4.1"
msgid "“Sabbe sattā marissanti, "
msgstr "“All beings will die, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.22:4.2"
msgid "maraṇantañhi jīvitaṃ; "
msgstr "for life ends with death. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.22:4.3"
msgid "Yathākammaṃ gamissanti, "
msgstr "They pass on according to their deeds, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.22:4.4"
msgid "puññapāpaphalūpagā; "
msgstr "reaping the fruits of good and bad. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.22:4.5"
msgid "Nirayaṃ pāpakammantā, "
msgstr "Those who do bad go to hell, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.22:4.6"
msgid "puññakammā ca suggatiṃ. "
msgstr "and if you do good you go to heaven. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn3.22:5.1"
msgid "Tasmā kareyya kalyāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "That’s why you should do good, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.22:5.2"
msgid "nicayaṃ samparāyikaṃ; "
msgstr "investing in the future life. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.22:5.3"
msgid "Puññāni paralokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "The good deeds of sentient beings "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.22:5.4"
msgid "patiṭṭhā honti pāṇinan”ti. "
msgstr "support them in the next world.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
